        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "216d33a8-5cfd-4ec2-893c-0a64f4982cde",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "External Remote Services"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1133"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "External Remote Services is Yayo's highest-frequency and most consistently observed technique at 31 reports — the actor gains entry to victim environments through internet-facing RDP gateways, VPN appliances, and remote management services using stolen domain and local credentials. This node anchors all post-access operations, with RDP-based lateral movement (9 reports) serving as the actor's primary pivot technique and Telegram providing the C2 channel for ongoing operations."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
